    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>You either create or destroy water.</p>\n<p><strong>Create Water.</strong> You create up to 10 gallons of clean water within range in an open container. Alternatively, the water falls as rain in a 30-foot &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} within range, extinguishing exposed flames in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Destroy Water.</strong> You destroy up to 10 gallons of water in an open container within range. Alternatively, you destroy fog in a 30-foot &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} within range.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you create or destroy 10 additional gallons of water, or the size of the &amp;Reference[cube]{cube} increases by 5 feet, for each slot level above 1st.</p>\n</div>",
